<div class="ampliance_layout layout4">
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap flex-column">

        <h2 class="title-block">
            <span class="title-text">Regimen Building with Retinoids</span>
        </h2>

        <div class="d-flex flex-wrap flex-column flex-xl-row justify-content-xl-between">

            <div class="image-block-1 d-none d-xl-block image-block">

            </div>

            <div class="text-content d-flex justify-content-start">
                    <div class="amp_partial text-block single-column">
                        <p>So now that we&rsquo;ve covered more about retinoids, how they work, and some key regimen tips, how do you choose the right retinoid for you and your skin concern? Again, pairing retinoids in a skincare regimen starts by gradually incorporating by strength, depending on whether you&rsquo;re a beginner, intermediate, or an advanced user of retinoids.<br><br>To target the following concerns, we recommend the following pairings:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Beginning Signs of Aging</strong> - Retinoids for early signs of aging include <a href="../retinol-02-in-squalane-serum-100439"><u>Retinol 0.2% in Squalane</u></a>. This option provides the well-studied retinol in a simple oil format. <a href="../granactive-retinoid-2-emulsion-serum-100419"><u>Granactive Retinoid 2% Emulsion</u></a>: These are next-generation retinoids available in two textures. Combine with <a href="../multi-peptide-ha-serum-100613"><u>Multi-Peptide + HA Serum</u></a>, an age-supporting peptide serum that does a little bit of everything for your skin and <a href="../caffeine-solution-5-egcg-eye-serum-100412"><u>Caffeine Solution 5% + EGCG</u></a>, a water-based serum that reduces the look of puffiness and dark circles in the eye contour.<br><br></li>
<li><strong>Advanced Signs of Aging</strong> - Retinoids for mature skin include <a href="../granactive-retinoid-5-in-squalane-serum-100421"><u>Granactive Retinoid 5% in Squalane</u></a>, or <a href="../retinol-1-in-squalane-serum-100441"><u>Retinol 1% in Squalane</u></a> for intermediate users or the new <a href="../retinal-02-emulsion-100646"><u>Retinal 0.2% Emulsion</u></a> for advanced users. Pair with <a href="../multi-peptide-ha-serum-100613"><u>Multi-Peptide + HA Serum</u></a>, and <a href="../multi-peptide-eye-serum-100620"><u>Multi-Peptide Eye Serum</u></a>, a multi-technology peptide eye serum to target signs of aging around the eye.<br><br></li>
<li><strong>Texture + Uneven Skin Tone</strong> - To use retinoids for skin texture and tone, we recommend pairing with <a href="../glycolic-acid-7-exfoliating-toner-100418"><u>Glycolic Acid 7% Exfoliating Toner</u></a> and the <a href="../niacinamide-10-zinc-1-serum-100436"><u>Niacinamide 10% + Zinc 1%</u></a>. The Niacinamide 10% + Zinc 1% improves skin smoothness and brightness, while Glycolic Acid 7% Exfoliating Toner exfoliates the skin's surface to improve the look of skin texture. Note, if you wish to use Retinoids alongside Direct Acids such as Glycolic Acid 7% Exfoliating Toner, we recommend using them on <strong>alternate evenings</strong> and waiting until your skin has adjusted to one ingredient before incorporating the other. This will help to reduce the risk of increased skin sensitivity.</li>
</ul>
